docs.name: ANOIX: American Century Small Cap Growth Fund - Investo
docs.description:
The investment seeks long-term capital growth.
 Under normal market conditions, the fund invests at least 80% of its assets in small cap companies. The portfolio managers consider small cap companies to include those with a market capitalization that does not exceed that of the largest company in the Russell 2000 Growth Index. The portfolio managers look for stocks of smaller-sized companies they believe will increase in value over time, using an investment strategy developed by American Century Investments.

docs.name: LDMCX: Lord Abbett Developing Local Markets Fd - Cl C
docs.description:
The investment seeks high total return.
 The fund normally invests at least 80% of net assets in instruments that provide investment exposure to the currencies of, and in fixed income instruments denominated in the currencies of, emerging markets at the time of purchase. It may invest up to 15% of its total assets in high yield debt securities. The fund's average portfolio duration is not expected to exceed eight years. It is non-diversified.

docs.name: FIGWX: First Amer Large Cap Growth Oppty Cl Y
docs.description:
The investment seeks long-term growth of capital.
 The fund invests at least 80% of net assets in common stocks of large-capitalization companies, defined as companies that have market capitalizations of $5 billion or greater at the time of purchase. Its sub-adviser invests in companies that it believes exhibit the potential for superior growth based on factors such as above average growth in revenue and earnings, strong competitive position, strong management, and sound financial condition. The fund may invest up to 15% of its total assets in non-dollar denominated equity securities of non-U.S. issuers.

docs.name: PSBCX: Virtus Balanced Fund Class C
docs.description:
The investment seeks reasonable income, long-term growth of capital and conservation of capital.
 The fund normally invests at least 65% of total assets in common stocks and fixed income securities of both U.S. and foreign issuers, including issuers in 'emerging market' countries, and may invest in companies of any size. It generally invests approximately 60% in equity securities and 40% in fixed income securities. Normally, the fund's dollar-weighted average duration will range between two and eight years.
